byline.original: By JACK EWING and JULIA WERDIGIER

abstract: Deutsche Bank reported a profit of $1.1 billion, a big rebound from a $1.6 billion loss a year earlier. UBS, which was hurt by a trading scandal that cost it $2.3 billion, saw its earnings fall 39 percent.

lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT - As European officials struggle to find a solution to the sovereign debt crisis, two of the region's largest financial firms continue to deal with the fallout from the market turmoil.
